God is limitless.

18:34.405 --> 18:36.167
But that's not the primary thing we learn about him here.

18:36.527 --> 18:39.090
We also see that he is self-revealed.

18:39.330 --> 18:39.953
I love this.

18:40.375 --> 18:47.090
It tells us in Romans 1.20 that through his creation, God's invisible attributes, namely his eternal power and his divine nature,

18:47.330 --> 18:50.374
are clearly perceived ever since the creation of the world and the things that have been made.

18:50.614 --> 18:51.956
So we are without excuse.

18:52.316 --> 18:54.980
What this is telling us is God is self-revealing.

18:55.060 --> 19:01.088
Nobody stumbled upon God, like the unknown wonder of the world, and they began to publish it so they could get a bunch of popularity.

19:01.108 --> 19:01.789
That's not what happened.

19:01.829 --> 19:05.454
Nobody arrived at this revelation by themselves.

19:05.474 --> 19:10.340
God was already revealing himself all along, but that's not the key thing that Genesis wanted to tell us about him.

19:10.640 --> 19:11.922
We also learned that he's sovereign.

19:12.386 --> 19:24.103
When it says that he made the heavens and the earth, the thought there is heavens and earth encapsulate everything known in creation, as well as everything unknown in creation.

19:25.465 --> 19:30.753
God is the uncaused cause of all of it.

19:30.773 --> 19:33.317
He is the primary character of the cosmos.

19:34.038 --> 19:38.564
And yet, not only did he create it, he rules and reigns over it.

19:38.845 --> 19:39.666
He's sovereign.

19:39.938 --> 19:44.122
But that's also not the primary thing that we need to learn about who God is.

19:44.182 --> 19:54.574
In an effort to know who God is, what Genesis wants to let you know is that God is, according to this text, he should be known as creator.

19:55.575 --> 19:56.536
God is creator.

19:57.396 --> 20:00.700
That's the big title to understand about who God is.

20:03.483 --> 20:04.985
Which it took us all of one verse to figure that out.

20:05.025 --> 20:06.386
So now you're probably wondering,

20:06.754 --> 20:08.315
What is the rest of this chapter about?

20:08.336 --> 20:14.621
There are 31 more verses here, Kyle, and I'm not real sure if this is all described to us that he is creator in just one verse.

20:14.722 --> 20:16.683
What is the rest of this chapter actually going to explain?

20:17.024 --> 20:18.265
Well, it's important for you to understand.

20:18.545 --> 20:25.412
You need to understand that though the first verse gives you God's creative character, the rest of the verses give you God's creative nature, his creative nature.

20:25.432 --> 20:30.977
I remember growing up, we would go to this local restaurant in my hometown.

20:32.018 --> 20:36.242
And inside of it, there was a sign that said, never trust a skinny cook.

20:37.250 --> 20:43.558
Now I'm not saying that that's good advice, but what I am saying is my young mind could actually understand what it was describing.

20:43.598 --> 20:46.381
It was telling me that actions speak louder than words.

20:47.422 --> 20:52.809
And so what we need to understand is that ladies, if you want to confirm if he's a gentleman, you should see the way that he treats the wait staff when you go on a date.

20:54.151 --> 21:00.178
If you want to see if someone's a good leader, you should think about the way that their employees or followers speak about them.

21:00.642 --> 21:06.549
And if you want to understand what kind of creator God is, you need not only look at what he has created, you need to look at the way in which he created.

21:06.569 --> 21:07.170
Does that make sense?

21:08.191 --> 21:09.233
That's what this is about.

21:09.853 --> 21:13.197
It's going to tell you the way he created.

21:13.558 --> 21:16.141
And as we see it, we learn more about him.

21:16.862 --> 21:19.605
There are three things that we see very specifically.

21:20.046 --> 21:24.511
Verse two, it tells us, the earth was without form and void.

21:24.892 --> 21:26.834
And darkness is over the face of the deep, deep.

21:27.298 --> 21:30.882
The earth was what the Hebrew describes as tohu and bohu.

21:31.042 --> 21:33.744
It had no form and it had no fill.

21:34.125 --> 21:37.848
Another way of thinking about that is it had no structure and it had no substance.

21:37.868 --> 21:39.610
So what's God doing in this story?

21:40.191 --> 21:44.855
He is preparing a world, a place for people to live.

21:45.676 --> 21:48.559
And yet there's no structure and there's no substance.

21:48.579 --> 21:53.664
Meaning if we're gonna use an analogy of something like a house, there are no walls and there's no furnishing.

21:54.264 --> 21:55.826
So what then is there in this moment?

21:57.090 --> 21:57.871
A foundation.

21:58.471 --> 21:58.832
That's it.

21:59.452 --> 22:05.919
All that is here in this moment, according to verse two, is a foundation, something upon which you can build.

22:06.199 --> 22:09.683
It describes it as this chaotic, disordered, primordial water.

22:10.163 --> 22:11.064
But more on that next week.

22:11.645 --> 22:19.633
Naturally, what we need to ask is if God is going to build a home for all people, what then should he do next?

22:21.475 --> 22:22.235
What anyone would do?

22:23.016 --> 22:24.978
He should put structure in place.

22:25.378 --> 22:30.307
He should raise up some walls, which is exactly what we see in days one, two, and three.

22:31.429 --> 22:35.776
It says that he creates light and dark, sky and waters, and land and sea.

22:36.478 --> 22:40.945
But notice this, he doesn't just stop there because the walls of a house don't make a home, do they?

22:42.268 --> 22:44.572
It's what's inside that makes a home.

22:46.515 --> 22:50.322
There needs to be substance within the structure of God's creation.

22:51.522 --> 22:56.188
That's what makes it feel complete, which is exactly what God goes on to do next.

22:56.329 --> 22:57.090
It's incredible.

22:57.630 --> 23:02.497
God, in the first set of three days, provides all of the structure.

23:03.619 --> 23:07.344
And then in the second set of three days, He provides all of the substance.

23:07.364 --> 23:09.667
And the beauty of it is, it's not random.

23:10.528 --> 23:11.550
It's reflective.

23:12.451 --> 23:13.112
Here's what I mean.

23:13.252 --> 23:15.135
I think we can put this on the screen to help describe it.

23:16.276 --> 23:20.402
On day one, God created the structures of night and day.

23:22.274 --> 23:30.583
And correspondingly on day four, the first day of the second set of three, he creates the substance for that night and day.

23:30.603 --> 23:33.246
He creates the sun, the moon, and the stars.

23:34.228 --> 23:38.432
On day two, he puts the structure of the sky and waters.

23:38.893 --> 23:47.983
And on day five, the corresponding second day in the second set of three, he creates the substance of birds and fish to fill those skies and waters.

23:48.003 --> 23:48.544
Do you see it?

23:49.425 --> 23:50.386
And on day three,

23:50.530 --> 23:52.833
where he created the structure of land from the water.

23:53.354 --> 23:58.621
Day six, we see he creates the corresponding substance for that structure.

23:58.681 --> 24:02.045
He creates the beasts of the field in humans.

24:03.347 --> 24:03.968
Isn't that amazing?

24:04.409 --> 24:07.112
Like, do you see what God's trying to tell us about himself?

24:08.494 --> 24:11.258
Not that he's type A, even though he's clearly organized.

24:11.558 --> 24:14.122
What he's trying to say is that he's intentional.

24:14.142 --> 24:20.370
You see, God, he created the world intentionally, not indifferently.

24:20.834 --> 24:34.012
is a huge thing for us to consider because he isn't haphazard or disinterested in his creation, like some people believe, like some people think that God sure, he created everything, but he spun it like a top and then he left it to wobble around on its own.

24:34.212 --> 24:34.913
But that's not true.

24:35.074 --> 24:36.736
He is deeply invested.

24:36.936 --> 24:41.202
He is deeply intentional with the affairs of our world.

24:41.314 --> 24:44.400
He put all of this structure and he filled it with all of this substance.

24:44.500 --> 24:46.144
I should have brought this as an illustration.

24:46.344 --> 24:50.953
But it would be as if I gave you a vase structure and I filled it with flowers, substance.

24:50.973 --> 24:51.715
See what God did?

24:51.735 --> 24:56.143
He is producing the constructs of creation so that life can flourish.

24:57.265 --> 24:59.570
And we do this too.

25:00.002 --> 25:07.752
I don't know what kind of look you're going for in your house, and yet more than likely in your house, you're trying to strike some sort of vibe, whether it's mid-century modern or Scandinavian.

25:07.772 --> 25:13.178
I don't know what your thing is, but you are trying to structure and fill that space in a way that produces what?

25:14.119 --> 25:14.660
Flourishing.

25:15.641 --> 25:21.629
Maybe it's a playlist that you listen to whenever you go running, but no other playlist that someone has made is going to qualify.

25:21.689 --> 25:23.331
No, you must curate it yourself.

25:23.811 --> 25:25.874
You must structure what you want.

25:26.178 --> 25:31.527
the atmosphere of that playlist to play, and then you must fill it with your own songs, because that produces flourishing.

25:31.868 --> 25:33.591
Others of you, you've got a power outfit.

25:34.192 --> 25:35.254
You've worked really hard on it.

25:35.454 --> 25:42.767
You have structure together that, which is going to openly help you express the greatest levels of confidence you can have whenever you step into the world.

25:43.107 --> 25:45.191
We do this all the time.

25:45.451 --> 25:47.996
We organize our lives in a way that produces flourishing.

25:48.076 --> 25:51.762
I remember one of my college roommates, he was dating this girl around Christmas time,

25:52.226 --> 25:54.071
And he was really into her.

25:54.472 --> 25:55.354
He lacked her a whole lot.

25:55.615 --> 26:02.131
And so, in an effort to make sure that things would continue to go really well, he did the inexplicable.

26:02.231 --> 26:04.818
He rented a Christmas tree farm.

26:05.602 --> 26:06.583
which I didn't know you could do that.

26:07.004 --> 26:08.866
He rented a Christmas tree farm, but not just that.

26:09.086 --> 26:20.279
He also, he went and he purchased snowballs from a local snow cone shop, and then he ensured that the two of them could have a private snowball fight, just the two of them, in this Christmas tree farm, with no one else around.

26:20.559 --> 26:21.941
Why would he go to all of this trouble?

26:21.961 --> 26:24.604
Because that is the recipe for success, gentlemen.

26:24.844 --> 26:31.892
That's what it looks like to woo a woman and bring her into a relationship, except for the fact that their relationship ultimately ended.

26:32.113 --> 26:33.234
What you need to know

26:33.730 --> 26:40.840
is that he wanted to provide the structure and the substance that would ultimately lead them to a thriving and not just surviving type of relationship.

26:40.900 --> 26:41.822
God does the same thing.

26:42.503 --> 26:46.308
Now as I say that, I know that can feel really hard to believe for some of you.

26:47.009 --> 26:56.142
Because the truth of the matter is, you may hear that God is intentional, but what you experience in your own life, what is closest to your own reality is that he's very indifferent.

26:58.505 --> 27:00.068
You're here and you feel like, man, he doesn't see me.

27:00.568 --> 27:01.810
He didn't care about me.

27:02.978 --> 27:04.520
He doesn't listen to me.

27:04.700 --> 27:06.161
I've prayed the right prayers.

27:06.281 --> 27:08.383
I've been steadfast in the face of trial.

27:08.443 --> 27:10.105
I've pursued faithfulness.

27:10.165 --> 27:10.986
And what have I gotten forward?

27:11.006 --> 27:12.167
I've got nothing, Kyle.

27:12.808 --> 27:14.189
Nothing good has come to me.

27:14.249 --> 27:15.951
God has not been intentional.

27:16.151 --> 27:18.113
He has only been indifferent.

27:19.434 --> 27:20.856
If that's you, would you just hear me?

27:22.297 --> 27:24.579
It is not that God is indifferent towards you.

27:26.041 --> 27:31.186
In fact, it is that God is being extra intentional with you.

27:32.194 --> 27:49.036
Because for those times in life where things feel so complicated and they make no sense at all, God is often, not always, but often leading us into places we would not go so that we can grow.

27:50.838 --> 27:56.946
He does this all the time and he does it because he is a good father.

27:58.114 --> 28:05.950
I got to relate to this reality really clearly this last week because we took our little baby boy and we shipped him off to daycare for the very first time.

28:07.132 --> 28:09.136
And I'll just level with you.

28:09.717 --> 28:12.082
I wasn't excited about it at all.

28:12.290 --> 28:16.774
I would much rather keep him in our house and ensure that he never feels abandoned.

28:16.794 --> 28:18.255
He never feels unloved.

28:18.315 --> 28:20.757
And yet at the same time, I know, dude, you need to grow up.

28:20.817 --> 28:22.959
Like you need to realize that the world doesn't revolve around you.

28:22.979 --> 28:28.304
You got to learn how to socialize and share some toys and make sure that you actually are a good contributor to society.

28:28.324 --> 28:31.006
Like I've got to help you become what you're meant to become.

28:31.286 --> 28:33.649
And yet if you stay here, you're not going to be able to do that.

28:33.689 --> 28:34.349
And so what did we do?

28:34.609 --> 28:38.433
We led him to his inevitable doomsday, doomsday, and we shipped him off.

28:38.493 --> 28:39.394
We put him in daycare.

28:39.614 --> 28:42.276
And yet here was the thing, the night before we did it, Brooke and I,

28:42.256 --> 28:47.884
And both of us still, we felt this anxiety over like, man, we know it's right, but, gosh, it's so hard.

28:49.186 --> 28:51.129
Like, what if he feels abandoned by us?

28:51.269 --> 28:52.711
He's never been outside of our home.

28:52.751 --> 28:54.353
He's never been left by himself.

28:54.614 --> 28:55.755
What if he feels abandoned?

28:58.679 --> 29:07.912
Well, he doesn't know this, but we've always got an eye on him because we literally have a live feed into his classroom.

29:07.932 --> 29:09.074
What if he feels unloved?

29:09.762 --> 29:13.408
Like, what if he gets dropped in a place he knows nothing about, and he totally feels unloved?

29:13.428 --> 29:24.386
Well, he may feel that way, but the reality is we look high and low for the best daycare possible, and we tested them thoroughly to make sure they would take care of our boy.

29:26.088 --> 29:30.455
And in those moments when he feels like mom and dad are never gonna show up, we know.

29:31.637 --> 29:37.106
Five o'clock's coming, and we're gonna be there waiting for you, ready to pick you up and take you home.

29:37.858 --> 29:42.363
I think God feels very similar to you in your moment of pain and difficulty.

29:43.184 --> 29:51.313
I think he dreads sending you into the wilderness, but he wants us to know when you feel abandoned, I've got an eye on you.

29:51.653 --> 29:54.616
When you feel unloved, I've already gone before you.

29:54.917 --> 29:56.398
And when you're worried, I'll never show up.

29:56.879 --> 29:57.359
Don't worry.

29:58.500 --> 29:59.982
I'm waiting for the moment to come.

30:00.823 --> 30:01.624
That's who he is.

30:02.325 --> 30:05.428
Like God, he is intentional.

30:05.969 --> 30:07.250
He is not indifferent.

30:07.874 --> 30:15.065
And we see this expressed not just as he declares it to us, but as he exemplifies it to us through the person of Jesus.

30:15.205 --> 30:20.032
Jesus, we know in Hebrews 12 to for the joy that was set before him, he endured the cross.

30:20.173 --> 30:20.733
Do you see that?

30:21.394 --> 30:25.060
He entered into immense difficulty, the likes of which you will never understand.

30:26.222 --> 30:29.467
And he despised its shame and now he is sitting at the right hand of the throne of God.

30:29.687 --> 30:34.835
You see Jesus himself, he understood sometimes it's got to get harder before it gets better.

30:36.137 --> 30:36.978
Sometimes

30:37.442 --> 30:42.047
The path to life goes to the valley of death.

30:43.869 --> 30:46.051
God is intentional with you, I promise.

30:46.091 --> 30:50.075
He is declaring it from Genesis 1, and he is declaring it to you today.

30:50.976 --> 30:53.999
And this would have been something that the ancient Israelites would have been processing themselves.

30:54.039 --> 31:01.507
Like that idea of man is God actually going to lead me through difficulty for my own development.

31:01.547 --> 31:04.530
The reality is they would have been chewing on this too.

31:05.122 --> 31:11.890
Contextually, you need to know the book of Genesis was written by Moses and it was given to him by God.

31:12.226 --> 31:16.630
whenever he had led the Israelites out of Egyptian slavery and into the wilderness.

31:16.650 --> 31:17.431
They're Mount Sinai.

31:17.451 --> 31:24.657
And so what he's doing is Moses is teaching these same truths to a group of people that have just been liberated out of captivity.

31:24.677 --> 31:26.138
They are a group of refugees.

31:26.158 --> 31:29.401
They are 2 million in number, men, women, and children.

31:29.661 --> 31:36.287
And what he is declaring to them is that yes, you may have been in Egypt, it may have been if hard, but God has come to get you out.

31:36.587 --> 31:39.650
And yet, here's the thing that we see as we continue to read into the story.

31:39.690 --> 31:42.212
We know that God looks at him and he says, man, yeah,

31:42.192 --> 31:47.639
They're set free of their circumstance, and yet their circumstance has really done a number on them.

31:47.659 --> 31:51.384
Like, yeah, I got them out of Egypt, but now I gotta get Egypt out of them.

31:52.165 --> 31:53.788
That's what we see as he keeps going.

31:54.028 --> 32:00.356
He realizes they have been conditioned into believing some lies that they need to unlearn.

32:01.037 --> 32:05.904
And so to help them unlearn them, what we see is he continues to speak.

32:07.666 --> 32:10.610
And he speaks to them in a principle that reminds them, hey,

32:11.522 --> 32:13.925
In Egypt, you were valued for what you do.

32:14.606 --> 32:18.972
You were valued, it correlated with how many bricks you can make for Pharaoh.

32:19.793 --> 32:23.338
But now, you're not valued for what you do, you're valued for who you are.

32:24.440 --> 32:26.062
Because God wants them to know what he wants you to know.

32:26.783 --> 32:29.647
God created human beings, not human doings.

32:30.948 --> 32:33.892
God created human beings, not human doings.

32:34.012 --> 32:37.657
That's why we read in verse five, and there was evening and morning the first day.

32:37.677 --> 32:41.042
And then we read in verse eight, and there was evening and morning the second day.

32:41.826 --> 32:44.330
In verse 13, there was evening and morning the third day.

32:44.350 --> 32:47.114
Isn't that crazy mind blowing?

32:49.959 --> 32:57.430
Maybe it doesn't strike us as such because we don't realize just how subtly significant what we're reading here actually is.

32:57.710 --> 33:09.068
And yet this is a massive point of importance because what God is saying is he is saying, you're valued for who you are, not what you do.

33:09.208 --> 33:10.450
Let me describe it to you like this.

33:10.978 --> 33:12.079
What do you do in your mornings?

33:12.100 --> 33:13.662
What do your mornings represent in your life?

33:16.245 --> 33:18.248
More than likely, they represent things like stress.

33:19.029 --> 33:22.213
Stress over the fact that it's busy season and your boss has high expectations.

33:23.235 --> 33:28.101
Anxiety, because you know you gotta have that conversation today and you are dreading having that conversation.

33:29.122 --> 33:32.908
Dread, because you woke up to 15 emails even when people should have been sleeping.

33:32.948 --> 33:35.811
Somehow they're still working and now you've gotta answer all of this stuff.

33:36.733 --> 33:40.658
The mornings often represent productivity, performance,

33:41.410 --> 33:42.091
Demand.

33:42.111 --> 33:45.454
Now, what do the evenings represent?

33:46.655 --> 34:04.392
The evenings represent kicking your feet up, curling up on the couch, winding down at the end of a long day with some good food, maybe a glass of wine, making sure that before you hit the hay, you open a book or you watch that show that you're interested in.

34:04.432 --> 34:10.418
The evening represents rest, peace, supply.

34:11.042 --> 34:12.704
That's why you look forward to it so much.

34:12.744 --> 34:15.087
That's why you're watching the clock and you can't wait to get out at five.

34:15.427 --> 34:18.251
You know, man, that's where rest is found.

34:18.691 --> 34:23.016
We live in a world that orders our days morning to evening, but God is looking at them.

34:23.037 --> 34:24.078
He's saying, no, no, no, no, no.

34:24.538 --> 34:26.220
Our day is ordered opposite.

34:26.240 --> 34:31.307
Our day is ordered evening to morning because I don't want you working for rest.

34:31.447 --> 34:33.669
I want you working from rest.

34:35.351 --> 34:40.818
I don't want you waking up and feeling all the rush and demand of having to go and do.

34:41.506 --> 34:51.568
I want you waking up and feeling the blessing that you are perfectly accepted by way of who you are, apart from anything you do.

34:54.896 --> 34:57.682
Genesis 127 tells us something really important about our value.

34:58.434 --> 35:00.337
It says, so God created man in his own image.

35:00.377 --> 35:02.421
In the image of God, he created a male and female.

35:02.441 --> 35:03.222
He created them.

35:03.262 --> 35:06.348
This is an idea in theological circles known as the Amago Day.

35:06.368 --> 35:08.271
We're going to spend a lot more time talking about it next week.

35:08.291 --> 35:15.584
So if I don't cut every angle on this for you, then just come back next week because we're going to talk extensively about this.

35:15.604 --> 35:21.554
But one thing you have to understand about the Amago Day is it's describing to you where your worth comes from.

35:21.954 --> 35:26.059
You see, it's saying that your self-worth is not rooted in what you do, it's rooted in who you are.

35:26.119 --> 35:27.260
So who does God say you are?

35:27.280 --> 35:29.864
God is saying that you are made in His image.

35:31.145 --> 35:34.389
That word image in the Hebrew is the word Selam.

35:35.911 --> 35:40.116
It's T-S-E-L-E-M. Selam.

35:40.136 --> 35:45.202
And the thought there is it represents an image or an idol.

35:45.826 --> 35:47.528
Literally, God has made you an idol.

35:47.548 --> 35:52.995
That's why He takes so much issue with there being idols of other gods in the world because He has already filled the world with so many idols.

35:53.015 --> 35:54.137
He has filled it with me and you.

35:55.058 --> 36:01.326
You are a representative of His likeness everywhere you go.

36:01.346 --> 36:07.474
You are a living, breathing, walking, talking representation of who He is.

36:07.874 --> 36:10.358
and there is no higher calling than that.

36:10.598 --> 36:13.463
You are distinctly different than the rest of creation.

36:13.503 --> 36:17.149
You are set apart because this is God's purpose for your life.

36:17.269 --> 36:33.635
It is not only to know him, it's to make him known, which means your sense of significance, whatever sense of significance you find and whatever it is you accomplish, you don't need it because God has already declared you as significant.

36:34.557 --> 36:35.378
When you don't

36:35.522 --> 36:42.210
feel like you matter because you don't have enough zeros on your paycheck or you don't have enough letters behind your name.

36:42.531 --> 36:47.277
You don't need to matter anymore because the truth of the matter is God has already declared that you matter.

36:48.158 --> 36:54.065
Whenever you feel like you're not as important as you want to be, you need no.

36:54.105 --> 37:02.956
It doesn't take thousands or tens of thousands or hundreds of thousands of followers to declare to you that you're an important person because God has already declared you are important.

37:02.977 --> 37:04.178
Does that make sense to you?

37:04.642 --> 37:05.804
This is so vital.

37:06.785 --> 37:08.568
Now as I say this, here's the thing that I know.

37:08.608 --> 37:22.209
I know that so many Christians in the room, so if you're not a believer, then just give me a minute, because I gotta have a family talk with some of my brothers and sisters, so many Christians in the room, they hear, yeah, I'm made in the image of God, and their brain turns off.

37:23.571 --> 37:25.655
They're like, yeah, I know that, I got that, Colin, thank you.

37:25.675 --> 37:28.920
I know that I'm valued for who I am and I'm valued for what I do, thanks.

37:29.120 --> 37:33.106
But here's the reality, if you know it, then why don't you live like it?

37:34.338 --> 37:37.363
Why is it that you have so much insecurity?

37:37.643 --> 37:39.967
Why is it that you live with so much false humility?

37:40.307 --> 37:48.921
Why is it that you have this deep rooted fear of the future that you're trying to control specific outcomes that you are so performative in Christian circles?

37:49.021 --> 37:49.983
Why are you doing it?

37:50.003 --> 37:55.191
That is a declaration that you do not understand where your value comes from.

37:55.431 --> 37:59.397
Because if you knew God gives my value, you wouldn't be looking to the world to give you anymore.

38:00.579 --> 38:02.322
You would understand where

38:02.434 --> 38:07.019
Your value is found, which follow me, and this is important.

38:09.302 --> 38:14.568
If you're struggling with this, it means you find greater worth in what you can make of yourself than what God can make of yourself.

38:19.174 --> 38:21.417
You already have value, Christian.

38:22.778 --> 38:23.579
Please live like it.

38:25.121 --> 38:29.426
You are overestimating your ability to think you can add anything to your worth.

38:30.754 --> 38:37.125
because not only did God give you worth at creation, he redignified your worth at salvation.

38:37.846 --> 38:42.795
He showed you, I made you right, you screwed it up, and I came to make you right again.

38:46.341 --> 38:48.745
You should be able to find rest in that truth.

38:48.765 --> 38:51.890
That should lead you to a place where you're able to take a load off.

38:52.834 --> 38:55.857
And the reason I know that is because in that truth, God rests himself.

38:55.917 --> 38:58.941
That's what we see as we come to the end of this passage.

38:59.001 --> 39:02.665
We see in Genesis two, one through three, I'm gonna read it again because it's just important.

39:02.685 --> 39:05.388
It says, that's the heavens and the earth, they were finished and all the hosts of them.

39:05.548 --> 39:07.751
And on the seventh day, God finished his work that he had done.

39:07.991 --> 39:11.055
And he rested on the seventh day from all his work that he had done.

39:11.115 --> 39:17.542
So God blessed the seventh day and he made it holy because on it, God rested from all his work that he had done in creation.

39:18.843 --> 39:21.106
I would have loved to have taught this.

39:21.570 --> 39:30.704
in a lecture kind of format, in a smaller room where we could put up things and I could draw them out for you because Genesis 1 is so poetically beautiful.

39:30.744 --> 39:38.617
There's so much happening in the literature of how Moses wrote this inspired by the Spirit, which unfortunately we just don't have time to get into.

39:38.857 --> 39:49.554
But one thing that you need to know is there is this striking element all throughout this chapter where we move in this rhythm of working to resting.

39:49.890 --> 39:50.971
working to resting.

39:50.991 --> 39:57.879
You see it, it says that God spoke, it was good, morning and evening, the day ended.

39:58.340 --> 40:00.022
And that happens again and again and again and again.

40:00.062 --> 40:04.747
Until day seven.

40:04.767 --> 40:07.851
Day seven is the day that never ends.

40:09.653 --> 40:16.301
Day seven is not marked by any conclusive commentary.

40:16.321 --> 40:17.362
It seems

40:18.370 --> 40:21.433
like this never-ending day of rest.

40:21.633 --> 40:28.361
Which I know some of you hear that and you're like, oh man, I've been on the fence about Christianity, but if that's what I'm signing up for, put me in, coach.

40:28.741 --> 40:39.813
That's where so many of you are at, because you would love to jump into something where it affords you a little self-care treatment, a day at the spa, a little retail therapy, maybe a golf trip with the boys.

40:40.093 --> 40:41.034
That's not what this is talking about.

40:41.875 --> 40:44.818
You see, we often mistake godly rest for worldly rest.

40:45.250 --> 40:47.555
But here's the difference in the two, and I want you to catch this.

40:47.916 --> 40:51.683
Worldly rest, it just wants to escape the sadness of reality.

40:52.465 --> 40:55.191
But Godly rest, the kind of rest that God himself does.

40:55.992 --> 40:59.540
It wants to enjoy the goodness of reality.

41:00.562 --> 41:02.706
Worldly rest wants to escape the sadness of it all.

41:03.170 --> 41:06.835
But Godly rest wants to enjoy the goodness of it all instead.

41:06.895 --> 41:10.801
That's why seven times he declares, this is good, this is good, this is good.

41:11.141 --> 41:16.068
Not because he did the job, like the Holy Spirit doesn't roll up and be like, man, like that lion, nice job, love what you did with the hair.

41:16.088 --> 41:17.710
Like that's not the way that this is working out.

41:18.231 --> 41:20.634
He looks at it and he says, it's not good because it's complete.

41:21.055 --> 41:26.863
It's good because it's from me.

41:28.145 --> 41:31.730
We have this idea when we read about the Garden of Eden that it's perfect.

41:31.938 --> 41:34.061
But that's not an ancient Near Eastern idea.

41:34.963 --> 41:38.328
They would not have assumed it was perfect because that would mean you could understand the end of it.

41:39.029 --> 41:41.113
But you cannot understand the end of God's goodness.

41:41.794 --> 41:44.137
It goes on and on and on and on.

41:44.318 --> 41:49.426
And his goodness is one which there is a total absence of evil and the total presence of himself.

41:50.267 --> 41:53.232
And the beauty of this is this day does an end.

41:53.873 --> 41:58.380
God has invited us into a story where we enjoy him forever.

41:58.861 --> 41:59.762
Isn't that amazing?

42:02.466 --> 42:08.614
Last story, last point, God created life to enjoy, not just endure.

42:10.657 --> 42:11.218
No last story.

42:17.967 --> 42:23.215
When I was sitting with TA at lunch that day, he looked at me and he asked me what I was doing with my life.

42:24.516 --> 42:25.698
And I was struck to the core.

42:25.758 --> 42:27.621
I didn't know what I was doing with my life.

42:30.585 --> 42:31.506
And then he,

42:31.650 --> 42:32.852
extended an invitation.

42:33.953 --> 42:40.061
He said, hey, when you feel like God makes it clear for you what you're supposed to be doing, why don't you give me a call?

42:41.944 --> 42:43.786
Because I'd love to bring you on staff here with me.

42:45.829 --> 42:52.658
And in that moment, I went from crisis to clarity in a world where I felt so much

42:52.738 --> 42:57.546
confusion about what I was supposed to be doing so much so that I was doing everything instead.

42:57.606 --> 43:01.914
In that moment, I felt like I had crystal clarity of what my purpose was.

43:01.954 --> 43:09.727
It wasn't just a work in this ministry to sign up for vocational, full-time, lifelong church work.

43:09.767 --> 43:11.851
That's not what I felt clarity of.

43:12.732 --> 43:16.178
What I felt clarity of from God is a process to the offer.

43:16.674 --> 43:25.267
of leaving everything else behind and stepping in to what God was doing through this ministry by way of his gospel.

43:25.347 --> 43:28.932
What I felt was purpose.

43:28.952 --> 43:32.798
I knew my life is meant to make him known.

43:32.838 --> 43:35.682
It's to know him and it's to make him known.

43:35.742 --> 43:41.691
That is the same offer on the table for you, friend.

43:43.053 --> 43:43.794
You're here.

43:44.034 --> 43:45.716
And I don't know what your world feels like.

43:45.756 --> 43:48.260
Maybe you've entered in the new year and you're pumped.

43:48.280 --> 43:49.221
Like you're so excited.

43:49.241 --> 43:52.065
You've got great goals and you're already checking them down.

43:52.105 --> 43:58.975
Like every single day on your calendar, you're checking off whatever it is you're trying to stay true to and build the habit of.

43:59.115 --> 44:01.419
But others of you, you're not here excited for the new year.

44:01.679 --> 44:03.922
You're here and you're concerned about it.

44:04.386 --> 44:08.250
because already three weeks in, you know the sins of your past.

44:08.270 --> 44:09.752
They're already here in the present.

44:09.772 --> 44:12.535
They're already walking with you today.

44:12.635 --> 44:14.677
And so you're wondering, man, is it already too late?

44:14.717 --> 44:16.499
Have I ruined 2026?

44:16.539 --> 44:22.706
The truth of the matter is you haven't ruined anything because Christ has fixed everything for those that place their faith in Him.

44:23.987 --> 44:27.151
You see, Jesus is not indifferent towards you.

44:27.171 --> 44:28.372
He is intentional about you.

44:28.832 --> 44:33.938
So intentional, in fact, that He left heaven, came to earth, and He moved with such purpose.

44:34.338 --> 44:38.763
such clarity of conviction that he would live the life you could not.

44:39.765 --> 44:43.149
And the way that he did it is he didn't just become a human being like us.

44:43.189 --> 44:45.532
He actually became the human doing that we cannot do.

44:45.812 --> 44:48.475
He did everything perfect in the life he lived.

44:48.676 --> 44:53.862
He accomplished all the law and the prophets in a way that led us into right relationship with God.

44:54.763 --> 44:55.884
But it isn't just that.

44:56.525 --> 44:57.266
What we see

44:57.442 --> 45:11.293
is that Christ, He has come to give us life but also life abundantly because you've been designed not just to enjoy this world but to enjoy the God of this world and where He is in His presence is the fullness of that kind of joy.

45:11.834 --> 45:13.618
Christ has come to restore you to that.

45:14.114 --> 45:15.836
So I don't know where you're at tonight.

45:16.197 --> 45:26.510
I don't know how you feel about this year, but here's what I would say, whatever story you're trying to write for the year that's still ahead, Christ, He wants to write a completely different story.

45:26.530 --> 45:28.934
And I promise you, that story will be better.

45:29.034 --> 45:30.716
Your purpose is to know God.

45:30.816 --> 45:36.924
And listen, when you know Him, you'll realize there is no one more worth knowing.

45:38.326 --> 45:39.387
Let me pray that you would know Him.

45:40.289 --> 45:41.330
God, thank you.

45:42.242 --> 45:43.384
Your word is so good.

45:43.464 --> 45:44.085
It's so beautiful.

45:44.125 --> 45:49.773
I love that we can just sit here and study it in a way where God doesn't just fill up our hearts.

45:49.813 --> 45:51.256
It enriches our minds.

45:51.276 --> 45:55.061
Like we realize just who you are, how good you are.

45:55.162 --> 46:00.950
And so God, what I'm praying right now is that God, you would work by way of your spirit.

46:03.094 --> 46:11.346
You would call people to place their faith in you if they have not, to rededicate their lives to you if they have not.

46:11.490 --> 46:16.197
and God to go faster and further with you than they may already be going.

46:16.959 --> 46:19.663
This is a truth God that doesn't just apply to some of us.

46:19.703 --> 46:21.786
This is a truth God that applies to all of us.

46:21.806 --> 46:29.058
And so God, I'm praying what my friend Natalie prayed earlier that God, you would work in a way that touches every single soul.

46:29.098 --> 46:31.642
Oh God, you can do that.

46:33.024 --> 46:34.106
God, you can do it.

46:35.228 --> 46:36.750
And so I'm praying for God.

46:36.890 --> 46:39.314
I am entering this year, expectant.

46:40.034 --> 46:48.004
Not just because God, I want all the fruit of a really awesome year, but because God, I want the one who makes all things awesome.

46:48.024 --> 46:48.704
I want you.

46:48.745 --> 46:51.067
And so God, come to us.

46:52.369 --> 46:53.590
Right now, I would invite you.

46:53.971 --> 47:04.323
Would you just invite God to invade your space, to enter into your mind, to move in your heart, to stir what need be awakened awake?

47:06.306 --> 47:09.810
There is a response in the room for us all, so let us respond.

47:10.082 --> 47:14.208
Not because I'm asking you to, but because he is worthy of it.

47:14.649 --> 47:15.810
What a God we have.

47:16.812 --> 47:18.014
What a God you are.

47:18.735 --> 47:20.097
There is no one higher.

47:20.357 --> 47:21.859
There is no one greater.

47:21.899 --> 47:24.063
There is no one more worthy.

47:24.363 --> 47:27.187
And so God, it is to you that we declare this year.

47:27.227 --> 47:32.255
This year from this night, it is yours.

47:32.836 --> 47:35.139
King Jesus, we follow you.

47:35.199 --> 47:37.002
We follow no one else.

47:37.523 --> 47:39.826
We want your spirit

47:40.066 --> 47:44.751
We want the life you have to give, so won't you come and give it to us right now?

47:44.771 --> 47:46.460
